Comment.MultiLanguageText: Use jogging to read initial limit values
Use jogging to read initial limit values

AttributeList.Text:
How to control and set capping station: 1) Start the machine 2) Use jog pos/neg in the capping station data block to rotate motor to read max and min value: ReadSensorMax and Read SensorMin. Based on these values update "SensorPosValMax..." and "SensorPosValMin..." 3) Move capping station using "MovingUP" and "MovingDOWN". The mechanism should stop top or bottom and confirm it with the change of the status "CSPositionUP" and "CSPositionDOWN". If it is constantly moving, it means that the value was not reached (too low for SensorPosValMin or too high for "SensorPosValMax").
IMPORTANT: - assembly of the mechanism needs to be the same, especially the position of the sensor - power supply for the sensor should be set to the exact voltage (5V) to provide repeteable readings
Things to implement: - Change sensor for limit switch - Improve mechanical design
E-STOP - always check!
DEBUG -- This block cycles the capping station
